  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Remove the green stalk<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> from the<strong> heritage beef tomato<span class=\"text-danger\">[es] </span></strong>and slice in half, horizontally</p><p>Use a spoon to scoop the flesh out of each tomato half (reserve the tomato flesh for later!)</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1653645132976-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1653645132976-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1653645132976-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1653645132976-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1653645132976-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>hollowed tomato halves</strong> to one side of a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and<strong> pepper</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven for an initial 10-15 min or until starting to soften</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1653645136946-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1653645136946-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1653645136946-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1653645136946-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1653645136946-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, drain the <strong>mozzarella</strong>, then pat and squeeze as much liquid out as you can with kitchen paper</p><p>Tear the <strong>drained mozzarella</strong> into small pieces and add them to a medium bowl</p><p>Add 3/4 of the<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><strong>soft cheese </strong>(save the rest for later!) to the bowl with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>olive oil </strong>and 2 tbsp<strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </strong>[3 tbsp] </span><strong>cold water</strong></p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong> and give it a good stir<strong> </strong>– this is your <strong>homemade stracciatella</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1653645141320-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
